Bola Bamigbola, Osogbo A hit-and-run driver has crushed a yet-to-be identified motorcyclist to death on the Osogbo-Gbongan Road in Osogbo, Osun State. The incident, which occurred on Saturday, according to eyewitnesses, was caused by dangerous driving. The motorist hit a Bajaj motorcycle that the deceased was travelling on and fled the scene immediately after realising what had happened. It was learnt that the motorcyclist died on the spot and his corpse was later evacuated by men of the Osun State Command of the Federal Road Safety Corps. When contacted, the Public Relations Officer, Osun Sector Command, FRSC, Agnes Ogungbemi, confirmed the accident. She said, “The nature of the accident was a hit-and-run and the probable cause is dangerous driving. One man riding a Bajaj motorcycle was hit and the driver of the vehicle that hit him fled the scene. The victim eventually died. “Our officers and men removed the corpse and deposited it in the morgue of the Ladoke Akintola University of Technology Teaching Hospital, Osogbo. His motorcycle has been taken to our office.” Copyright PUNCH. All rights reserved. This material, and other digital content on this website, may not be reproduced, published, broadcast, rewritten or redistributed in whole or in part without prior express written permission from PUNCH. Contact: theeditor@punchng.com 